Quick setup — if you’ve done this kind of thing before
https://github.com/saleeminfogit/herovired.git
Get started by creating a new file or uploading an existing file. We recommend every repository include a README, LICENSE, and .gitignore.

…or create a new repository on the command line
echo "# herovired" >> README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/saleeminfogit/herovired.git
git push -u origin main
…or push an existing repository from the command line
git remote add origin https://github.com/saleeminfogit/herovired.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main


Download
# Create a folder
$ mkdir actions-runner && cd actions-runner# Download the latest runner package
$ curl -o actions-runner-linux-x64-2.334.0.tar.gz -L https://github.com/actions/runner/releases/download/v2.334.0/actions-runner-linux-x64-2.334.0.tar.gz# Optional: Validate the hash
$ echo "048024cd2c848eb6f14d5646d56c13a4def2ae7ee3ad12122bee960c56f3d271  actions-runner-linux-x64-2.334.0.tar.gz" | shasum -a 256 -c# Extract the installer
$ tar xzf ./actions-runner-linux-x64-2.334.0.tar.gz
Configure
# Create the runner and start the configuration experience
$ ./config.sh --url https://github.com/saleeminfodevops/herovired --token CDQ2QZ4KODRFYCLKKRHJAJLKAAZ3E# Last step, run it!
$ ./run.sh
Using your self-hosted runner
# Use this YAML in your workflow file for each job
runs-on: self-hosted